If you do NOT know how to use a disassembler, know the basics of assembly language, hex editors, offsets and the basic commands:
CBW
MOV
LEA
PUSH
POPF
LES
Please don't bother with this. Cracking begins with a touch of Assembler. Using a disassembler or a hex editor demands some assembler lang knowledge. If you are not willing to put the time in; you'll get shit. It's also very difficult to find really decent Assembly lang text books any longer.

You can still run SoftIce under a DOS box. What you need to know is IF the executable is a packed program or else you're going to feel pretty stupid after 5 minutes!
32 & 64 bit programs all make the same calls for a integer solve as a serial number: you simply cut that call out and - no more serial # demand!
